    • Method Detail

      • intercept

        public java.lang.Object intercept(java.lang.Object targetObject,
                                  java.lang.reflect.Method targetMethod,
                                  java.lang.Object[] params,
                                  net.sf.cglib.proxy.MethodProxy proxy)
                           throws java.lang.Throwable

        Method interceptor, which in the case of Latency4J annotated methods will:

        • Create a latency monitor for either the category specified in the annotation, or an implicit category built from the name of the intercepted method.
        • Invoke LatencyMonitor.taskStarted() on the monitor instance.
        • Call the proxied method.
        • Invoke either LatencyMonitor.taskCompleted() or LatencyMonitor.taskErrored(Throwable) on the monitor instance post completion of the proxied method.

        Where the proxied method is not annotated, this method simply invokes the proxied method without any monitoring.

        Specified by:
        intercept in interface net.sf.cglib.proxy.MethodInterceptor
        Parameters:
        targetObject - The instance on which to invoke th e proxied method.
        targetMethod - The proxied method.
        params - The parameters with which to invoke the proxied method.
        proxy - CGLIB method proxy instance.
        Returns:
        The result of the proxied method.
        Throws:
        java.lang.Throwable
